This paper discusses the potential harms caused by AI systems and proposes measures to counteract them, which falls under the category of AI ethics and safety. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the need for governance processes and interpretable outcomes, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the importance of human-centered and context-sensitive implementation, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
